# Copy to .env locally. Do not commit real secrets.
#
# This file lives at the repository root and is bind-mounted into the container
# at /workspace/.env. At startup bin/chat's Lisp process reads it and sets each
# KEY=value into its own process environment, so shell commands the agent runs
# through run_shell inherit them. Variables already present in the environment
# are not overridden. Values are never logged (only the names that were set).
#
# Line forms: KEY=value, optionally `export KEY=value`, with optional matching
# single/double quotes around the value. Blank lines and # comments are ignored.

# Required for live OpenRouter chat/tool sessions (default backend).
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# Required for the Synthetic OpenAI-compatible chat/tool backend.
# Get a Synthetic API key; never commit a real value.
SYNTHETIC_API_KEY=

# Optional provider selector for non-chat entry points (bin/chat prefers flags):
#   openrouter (default) — uses OPENROUTER_API_KEY
#   synthetic — uses SYNTHETIC_API_KEY against Synthetic's OpenAI-compatible API
#   codex — ChatGPT/Codex *subscription* via local codex app-server (no API key)
# Prefer: bin/chat --backend codex --codex-home .codex-home
# HARNESS_BACKEND=openai and OPENAI_API_KEY / api.openai.com are NOT supported.
# HARNESS_BACKEND=openrouter

# Optional. Codex OAuth home when using the codex backend without --codex-home.
# CODEX_HOME=/workspace/.codex-home

# Required for the Claude Code CLI-only backend. On a logged-in machine, generate
# a long-lived subscription OAuth token with `claude setup-token`, then set it
# here. It is passed only to the Claude child process as CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN;
# never commit a real token or pass it as a command-line argument.
# CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=

# Optional. Exposed inside the container as GITHUB_TOKEN for git/gh and other
# tools the agent invokes via run_shell.
# GITHUB_TOKEN=

# Optional. Enables the web_search tool (Tavily Search API) for real-time web
# search. Get a free key at https://app.tavily.com (1,000 credits/month).
# TAVILY_API_KEY=
